This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   - Investigate and document a browser bug where display-p3 colors in SVG background images get clamped to sRGB when `background-repeat` is used (Chrome & Safari)
   - Write a blog post about the bug
   - Build homepage features: word count display, divider graphic component, card hover effects
   - Create a shared/reusable `drawStrokes` function to DRY up duplicated SVG stroke generation logic, inlined via Eleventy's JS bundling (not an external file)
   - Session rule: do not write code unless explicitly told to (relaxed as session progressed and user started requesting code changes)

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Display P3 / wide gamut color spaces in CSS and SVG
   - Browser SVG rasterization pipeline (intermediate sRGB buffer when tiling)
   - PNG ICC color profiles (cHRM/gAMA chunks) vs SVG color declarations
   - Eleventy/WebC component patterns: `webc:root="override"`, `webc:scoped`, `webc:keep`, `webc:bucket`
   - WebC `@text` uses JS function call syntax, not Nunjucks pipe syntax
   - `webc:keep` outputs script per component instance; `webc:bucket="components"` bundles once into layout
   - SVG filters: feTurbulence + feDisplacementMap for hand-drawn stroke effect
   - Adjacent sibling selector (`+`) broken by `<script>` tags between elements
   - Eleventy collections, filters, and `getBundle('js', 'components')`

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`src/blog/2026/display-p3-background-repeat-bug.md`**
     - Blog post about the P3 SVG background-repeat bug
     - Originally created at `src/blog/display-p3-background-repeat-bug.md`, moved to `2026/` subdirectory
     - Layout updated from `layouts/article.njk` to `layout-article.webc`
     - User heavily edited content, title, description after initial draft

   - **`eleventy.config.js`** — Added `totalWordCount` filter
     - Strips frontmatter (`rawInput` approach failed; uses rendered `content` via function call syntax)
     - Strips `<pre>` blocks and HTML tags, counts whitespace-separated words
     - Returns formatted string with `toLocaleString("en-US")`
     ```javascript
     conf.addFilter("totalWordCount", (posts) => {
       return posts.reduce((total, post) => {
         const raw = post.rawInput || "";
         const text = raw
           .replace(/^---[\s\S]*?---/, "")
           .replace(/```[\s\S]*?```/g, "")
           .replace(/<pre[\s>][\s\S]*?<\/pre>/gi, "")
           .replace(/<[^>]+>/g, "")
           .replace(/\s+/g, " ")
           .trim();
         return total + (text ? text.split(" ").length : 0);
       }, 0).toLocaleString("en-US");
     });
     ```

   - **`src/_components/home-contents-tertiary.webc`** — Blog/About callout cards on homepage
     ```html
     <div webc:root="override">
       <a href="/blog" class="card">
         <p>
           Since 2009, I've written ~<span
             @text="totalWordCount($data.collections.posts)"
           ></span>
           words on design, technology, and life on my blog which you can read here.
         </p>
       </a>
       <a href="/about" class="card">
         Or maybe you'd like to know things about me?
       </a>
     </div>
     <style webc:scoped="home-contents-tertiary">
       :host { display: flex; flex: 1; gap: var(--g-gutter); }
       .card { align-items: center; background: var(--color-accent-primary); color: var(--color-bg); display: flex; flex: 1; min-height: 200px; padding: 2rem; }
     </style>
     ```

   - **`src/_components/home-divider.webc`** — Randomized animated SVG stroke divider
     - Generates random bent strokes filling available width
     - Auto-redraws every 1000ms, redraws on resize (debounced 150ms)
     - Uses feTurbulence + feDisplacementMap SVG filter with random seed per draw
     - Uses `<script webc:keep>` (inline, only on pages that include the component)
     - Current full state:
     ```html
     <div webc:root="override">
       <svg aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"></svg>
     </div>
     <style webc:scoped="home-divider">
       :host { color: var(--color-accent-primary); display: block; height: 2rem; overflow: hidden; width: 100%; }
       svg { display: block; height: 100%; width: 100%; }
     </style>
     <script webc:keep>
       (function () {
         const el = document.querySelector(".home-divider");
         if (!el) return;
         const svg = el.querySelector("svg");
         function draw() {
           const w = el.offsetWidth;
           const h = el.offsetHeight;
           svg.setAttribute("viewBox", `0 0 ${w} ${h}`);
           svg.innerHTML = "";
           const defs = document.createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/svg", "defs");
           defs.innerHTML = `<filter id="divider-warp">
             <feTurbulence type="turbulence" baseFrequency="0.04" numOctaves="2" result="turbulence" seed="${Math.floor(Math.random() * 100)}" />
             <feDisplacementMap in="SourceGraphic" in2="turbulence" scale="3" xChannelSelector="R" yChannelSelector="G" />
           </filter>`;
           svg.appendChild(defs);
           const g = document.createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/svg", "g");
           g.setAttribute("filter", "url(#divider-warp)");
           svg.appendChild(g);
           const midY = h / 2;
           let x = 10 + Math.random() * 20;
           while (x < w - 10) {
             const len = 15 + Math.random() * 60;
             const angle = (Math.random() - 0.5) * 2.8;
             const dx = Math.cos(angle) * len;
             const dy = Math.sin(angle) * len;
             const startY = midY + (Math.random() - 0.5) * h * 0.4;
             const endX = x + dx;
             const endY = startY + dy;
             const bent = Math.random() < 1;
             let d;
             if (bent) {
               const t = 0.3 + Math.random() * 0.4;
               const mx = x + dx * t + (Math.random() - 0.5) * 12;
               const my = startY + dy * t + (Math.random() - 0.5) * 12;
               d = `M${x} ${startY}L${mx} ${my}L${endX} ${endY}`;
             } else {
               d = `M${x} ${startY}L${endX} ${endY}`;
             }
             const path = document.createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/svg", "path");
             path.setAttribute("d", d);
             path.setAttribute("stroke", "currentColor");
             path.setAttribute("stroke-width", 2 + Math.random() * 4);
             path.setAttribute("stroke-linecap", "butt");
             path.setAttribute("fill", "none");
             g.appendChild(path);
             x += 5 + Math.random() * 12;
           }
         }
         let resizeTimer;
         const intervalDuration = 1000;
         let interval = setInterval(draw, intervalDuration);
         window.addEventListener("resize", function () {
           clearTimeout(resizeTimer);
           clearInterval(interval);
           resizeTimer = setTimeout(function () {
             draw();
             interval = setInterval(draw, intervalDuration);
           }, 150);
         });
         draw();
       })();
     </script>
     ```

   - **`src/_components/home-contents-card.webc`** — Card component with hover stroke effects
     - Added `.strokes` SVG overlay (absolute positioned, z-index 2, below title z-index 3)
     - Scale effects on hover: title 1.05 (0.2s), graphic 1.02 (0.3s)
     - Strokes use edge-biased Y positioning and feTurbulence filter with unique IDs per card
     - Script uses `webc:bucket="components"` to avoid breaking adjacent sibling selectors
     - Current full state of script section:
     ```javascript
     document.querySelectorAll(".home-contents-card").forEach(function (card, i) {
